<br>
my 2cp  (sheesh I'm gonna go broke eventually)<br>
<br>
Cae/Shaunae <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uslylukk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slylukk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slyfukk Asskicker</span><br>  Posts: 235<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 5:53:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fodysseyxevfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Loots and Raids</span><hr size=1> ah ok Jora..<br>
You are talking about 2 comments i didnt say.<br>
<br>
I personally dont deal in specifics unless i know the whole deal.<br>
<br>
Please look back through my comments.<br>
<br>
I can say that all my comments come from lots and lots of experience with the same situations..<br>
<br>
And while i have been unable to raid as of the last few months, i have done a hell of alot of raiding, i have led raids, i have helped start policies with more then one guild. I also know how some of the simpler encounters go. I for one hope i can come back for raids sooner then later.. I miss it too damn much. <br>
<br>
AS far as the hostility from you... i dont quite understand why it came at me..but so be it.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ujoradelossian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jora Delossian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fellow Traveler of Norrath</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 7:50:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fodysseyxevfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Loots and Raids</span><hr size=1> I dount doubt you have a good deal of experience with EQ, with raiding, with whatever, Slylukk.  I just find it.... amusing, I suppose, that someone who hasn't been on the game for several months and is no longer an active participant in a guild, would come on that guild's message boards and tell that guild how its matters should be handled.  Regardless of your past standing in Odysseys or PL, you don't play EQ anymore, and I personally don't think it's appropriate the way you charge on the boards and tell the rest of us how it is.  Maybe you don't mean it that way, but if you &quot;look back through your comments,&quot; perhaps you'll see that's how you're coming across.<br>
<br>
It's something I've noticed of you since the day I gained acess to these boards.  It's really not that big of an issue for me, and normally I wouldn't say anything, but the other day I was pissed off and since I was blowing it all out, I let that out too.  Hell, ask any of the people I'm good friends with in game.  They'll tell you that I've yelled and ranted at them at one time or another, but the next day we were back to normal.<br>
<br>
So don't get me wrong; I don't have any sort of personal grudge against you.  If your RL works out enough so that you can get back on EQ, I look forward to getting to know you in game as a member of Odysseys.  Until then, good luck with whatever it is that you do.<br>
<br>
Jora <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bodysseyxev.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jaysondafearless>Jayson Dafearless</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fellow Traveler of Norrath</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 2:40:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fodysseyxevfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Loots and Raids</span><hr size=1> Just a thought not sure if the officers have something like this going on in the officers section of the boards. Seeing as how many of us are on different time zones, including officers and regular guild members, it might be helpful for the officers to have a list of guildies and what loot has been awarded to them lately, this in my opinion would help a lot in the decision making of who gets what loot. The officers will have access to this in case they are having a hard time deciding. Hell I have a hard time remembering what I did last week, I'm gonna go out on a limb here and assume that our officers are not gonna be able to remember offhand what loot everyone has gotten. And since some officers are only able to attend certain amount of raids, blah what i'm trying to say is that not all our officers are on at ALL our raids, thus they do not really know what each officer has awarded what to those in guild who participated in the recent raid. With this chart that I propose it would help out a lot and hopefully lessen the aslkjing about how it seems some peeps in guild are favorites over others and in how loot is distributed. Just my 2cp. Flame me as u like it's late and just thought I would put in a suggestion.<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120766"> J A Y S O N </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></center><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  58 M Y R M I D O N </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></center><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utuxtrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tuxtrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer of Odysseys</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 6:12:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fodysseyxevfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Loots and Raids</span><hr size=1> Ok i would like to step in here an say why i said random the loot. First of all  i was given the impression people from outside of guild helped with the kill, an it was under a small grp which i wasnt even involvd in. I was in gd at the time this all went down. Obviously i was wrong about this because people got really mad about it.<br>
<br>
Lodi is a easy kill an when people start questioning officers not at the kill it gets tricky via text. People cant fully explain who was camping what an who was all there for the kill. Lately lodi has been killed as soon as it spawns an many guilds are there even some trying to KS. I am the type of person that if i see other guild helping my guild do somethig then i feel they earned apiece of the pie also.<br>
<br>
The way i decide who gets the item is by rolling with other guild prior or after the kill. Rolling is evil way but nothing you can do about coming up with a solution to make both guilds happy at once w/o one feeling they got screwed over. <br>
<br>
When stuff like last week with maxum getting his shieldl ninja by other guild it becomes a grudge match. You cant expect officers to show up to all encounters like these, its like farming a uber rare mob in seb in a pickup grp an having officer decide who should get loot.<br>
<br>
Something like the scout is normally done with few guild members although sometimes you will encounter other guilds setting up to get it also. Scout becomes a race to see who can turn in bag an kill captain first. Many times this can be a huge problem of who has force first. When doing scout i try to be courtious to other guilds at the camp. If they have more than enough people to do kill captain i dont spam guild chat with tells for help with scout. If it looks like an equal race try to work something out with otheer guild before engagin battle.<br>
<br>
So many people have done scout it is impossible to keep a track record of how many each person has been to. When deciding loot it will be based on merit. People that have done scout once cant expect to get two bracers if some dont even have one. For the folks who really want two bracers then i say camp it an only use tells for people who already have bracer or dont need bracer to come help you kill it.<br>
<br>
Whoever was camping the mob is always considered a top candidate for loot from lodi or scout. It just boggling how  people get so upset over this loot. Lodi is average loot an people make it seem like your a gimp if ya dont have it. With a guild our status people should forget about lodi an aim for  something better, god knows there is items alot better out there specially with expansion.<br>
<br>
Tux<br>
